article.headline: Tigers Willingham scores 25, has 18 boards
article.linkText: Auburn routs Monmouth (N.J.) for 8th in a row
article.story:
AUBURN, Ala. (AP) -- Le'Coe Willingham had 25 points and a
career-high 18 rebounds to lead No. 21 Auburn to its eighth
straight win, 59-38 over Monmouth on Sunday.

Willingham shot 7-for-9 from the field and 11-for-12 from the
line, and Mandisa Stevenson added 12 points and 10 rebounds for the
Tigers (12-2).

Niamh Dwyer hit five 3-pointers and finished with 18 points for
Monmouth (4-5), which lost its fourth straight.

Jewonda Bright, Monmouth's leading scorer with a 14.1 average,
was limited to two points on 1-for-7 shooting.

Auburn scored the first 11 points and led 32-15 at halftime,
holding the Hawks to five field goals in the first half.

Monmouth's 15 first-half points were a season low.

Auburn opened the second half with a 13-5 run and led by as many
as 29 before coach Joe Ciampi pulled his starters.

Auburn limited Monmouth to 23 percent shooting, the fourth
straight game the Tigers held an opponent under 35 percent.
